      "id": 358427,
      "is_answer_order_important": false,
      "stimulus_html": "",
      "stem_html": "<p>The proton NMR spectrum is shown for a compound with the formula C<sub>5</sub>H<sub>9</sub>NO<sub>4</sub>. The infrared spectrum displays strong bands at 1750 and 1562 cm<sup>–1</sup> and a medium-intensity band at 1320 cm<sup>–1</sup>. The normal carbon-13 and the DEPT experimental results are tabulated. Draw the structure of this compound.</p>\n<table class=\"unnumbered\">\n<thead>\n<tr>\n<th><b>Normal Carbon</b></th>\n<th><b>DEPT-135</b></th>\n<th><b>DEPT-90</b></th>\n</tr>\n</thead>\n<tbody>\n<tr>\n<td>    14 ppm</td>\n<td>Positive</td>\n<td>No peak</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td> 16</td>\n<td>Positive</td>\n<td>No peak</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td> 63</td>\n<td>Negative</td>\n<td>No peak</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td> 83</td>\n<td>Positive</td>\n<td>Positive</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>165</td>\n<td>No peak</td>\n<td>No peak</td>\n</tr>\n</tbody>\n</table>\n<img src=\"https://exercises.openstax.org/rails/active_storage/blobs/proxy/eyJfcmFpbHMiOnsibWVzc2FnZSI6IkJBaHBBbndVIiwiZXhwIjpudWxsLCJwdXIiOiJibG9iX2lkIn19--fd35362eef37d1fef1e93baaaef42ec82f3bc336/OChem_13_EC_029.jpg\" alt=\"Proton spectrum of C 5 H 9 N O 4 shifts: 0, 1.3 (triplet), 1.8 (doublet), 4.3 (quartet), and 5.2 (quartet). Relative areas of 3, 3, 2, and 0.92 respectively.\">",
